cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this collection in research or production, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "skill-x: A composable collection of agent skills"
date-released: 2026-07-17
license: MIT
authors:
  - family-names: Majumdar
    given-names: Ansh
    alias: anshmajumdar
repository-code: "https://github.com/anshmajumdar/skill-x"
keywords:
  - agent
  - skills
  - llm
  - coding-agent
  - interpretability
  - linear-probes
  - delegation
  - multi-agent
  - self-evolution
description: |
  skill-x is a small, composable collection of agent skills
  covering four areas: full rigor task execution
  (think-like-gpt-5-6), delegation with cheap subagents
  (efficient-fable), mechanistic interpretability of coding-agent
  LLMs via linear probes (skill-zero), and a self-evolving rigor
  + delegation synthesis (super-skill).
